                        Selected LAPB Publications, 2001
     __________________________________________________________________

    1. Birkenheuer, D.,2001: Utilizing variational methods to incorporate
       a variety of satellite data in the LAPS moisture analysis,
       Preprints, 11th Conf. on Satellite Meteorology and Oceanography,
       Madison, WI, Amer. Meteor. Soc. Html, PDF, PostScript
    2. Birkenheuer, D., Shaw, B.L., Albers, S., and E. Szoke, 2001:
       Evaluation of local-scale forecasts for severe weather of July 20,
       2000. Preprints, 14th Conf. on Numerical Weather Prediction, Ft.
       Lauderdale, FL, Amer. Meteor. Soc. Html, PDF
    3. Birkenheuer, D., 2001: Expanding the variational methods in the
       LAPS moisture analysis. Preprints, 14th Conf. on Numerical Weather
       Prediction, Ft. Lauderdale, FL, Amer. Meteor. Soc. Html, PDF
    4. McGinley, J.A., 2001: Toward a surface data continuum: Use of the
       Kalman filter to create a continuous, quality controlled surface
       data set. Preprints, 18th Conf. on Weather Analysis and
       Forecasting, Ft. Lauderdale, FL, Amer. Meteor. Soc. PDF
    5. McGinley, J.A. and J.R. Smart, 2001: On providing a cloud-balanced
       initial condition for diabatic initialization. Preprints, 18th
       Conf. on Weather Analysis and Forecasting, Ft. Lauderdale, FL,
       Amer. Meteor. Soc. PDF
    6. Schultz, P. and S. Albers, 2001: The use of three-dimensional
       analyses of cloud attributes for diabatic initialization of
       mesoscale models. Preprints, 14th Conf. on Numerical Weather
       Prediction, Ft. Lauderdale, FL, Amer. Meteor. Soc. Html, PDF
    7. Shaw, B.L., J.A. McGinley, and P. Schultz, 2001: Explicit
       initialization of clouds and precipitation in mesoscale forecast
       models. Preprints, 14th Conf. on Numerical Weather Prediction, Ft.
       Lauderdale, FL, Amer. Meteor. Soc. PDF
    8. Shaw, B.L., E.R. Thaler, and E.J. Szoke, 2001: Operational
       evaluation of the LAPS-MM5 "hot start" local forecast model.
       Preprints, 18th Conf. on Weather Analysis and Forecasting, Ft.
       Lauderdale, FL, Amer. Meteor. Soc. PDF
     __________________________________________________________________

